  "title": "Change TUI bead list default filter from 'active' to 'all'",
  "agent_type": "developer",
  "description": "In src/agent_takt/tui/state.py, TuiRuntimeState.filter_mode defaults to FILTER_DEFAULT which excludes done beads. After a feature merge, all beads are done and the list panel appears empty \u2014 confusing for users who expect to see their work. Fix: change the default from FILTER_DEFAULT to FILTER_ALL in the TuiRuntimeState dataclass (state.py:144). FILTER_ALL includes done beads so the list is never empty when beads exist.",
